co.cask.coopr.http.handler

Class PluginHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cask.http.AbstractHttpHandler
      • co.cask.coopr.http.handler.AbstractAuthHandler
        • co.cask.coopr.http.handler.PluginHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    co.cask.http.HttpHandler

    @Path(value="/v2/plugins")
public class PluginHandler
extends AbstractAuthHandler
    Handler for plugin resource related operations, such as uploading resources, staging, and recalling resources, and syncing resources. Only a tenant admin can access these APIs.

        Add an automator type resource. For example, uploading a resource named "hadoop" of resource type "cookbook" for the automator type "chef-solo".

        responder - Responder for responding to the request

        resourceName - Name of the resource being uploaded

        Body consumer for streaming the contents of the resource to the plugin store

      • getAllAutomatorTypeModules

        @GET
@Path(value="/automatortypes/{automatortype-id}/{resource-type}")
public void getAllAutomatorTypeModules(org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.http.HttpRequest request,

                                       @PathParam(value="automatortype-id")
                                       String automatortypeId,

        Get a mapping of all resources of the given type for the given automator type. Request can optionally contain a 'status' http param whose value is one of 'active', 'inactive', 'staged', or 'recalled' to filter the results to only contain resource that have the given status.

        request - Request to get resources of the given type
        responder - Responder for responding to the request
        automatortypeId - Id of the automator type that has the resources
